A MOTHER and her daughter died in a car accident on Monday. Netcare 911 responded to reports of a crash on the R24, near Orient Hills in Magaliesburg. Spokesman Shawn Herbst said: “Reports from the scene indicate that a light motor car and a light delivery vehicle were involved in a collision.” Herbst said paramedics assessed the scene and found that none of the occupants of the bakkie were not hurt. “A woman and young girl from the car died on scene, and another man and a little girl sustained moderate injuries,” said Herbst. They were treated at the scene by an advanced life support paramedic.